<GUIClass name="SHP_JobControllerForm" id="0f46637b-8169-423f-ba8e-f583749e4268">
    <superclass name="CM_BaseForm"/>
    <transient/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>TECHINICAL DETAILS CURRENT SHIP JOB CONTROLLER 

The Ship Job Controller is drawn using a controller class SHP_JobControllerController ( rename if necessary)

Everything Is drawn on the forms  scrollable drawing frame

- the main frame draws the jobs
- the Vertical Label frame has the Ship graphics drawn on it
-- Uses this helper class to draw the ship CMUI_DrawCellVoyageOverview
- the horizontal Label frame has the time line graphics drawn on it
-- Uses this helper class to draw the time line  CMUI_DrawScrollTimeLine

All jobs are drawn based on each jobs stats.

- Stats are calculated by creating a CMIF_VoyageStats object  and then calling  CMIF_VoyageStats::getStats
-- This creates a CMIF_JobSheetStats for each crane with a collection of all CMIF_JobStats objects
-- CMIF_JobStat object has info 
--- actualEndTime
--- actualStartTime
--- targetEndTime ( looks at the current crane rates per hour  and type of boxes to work this out) see CM_VoyageJob::getEstJobTimeForJobStats
--- targetStartTime
--- completedMoves
--- incompleteMoves
--- incompleteOverDimesion
--- incompleteSLOD SL = Single Lift, TL = Twin Lift, OD= On deck, UD = Under Deck
--- incompleteSLUD
--- incompleteTLOD
--- incompleteTLUD
--- num20s
--- num40s


NOTE : the tool tips for jobs gets most of its values from the CMIF_JobStat object

SHP_JobControllerController currently drawns for one voyage by drawing each cranes job sheet using helper class SHP_CraneJobDrawingController

            - i.e. SHP_JobControllerController:: allJobDrawControllers this dict keyed by crane. If this was changed to drawn multiple voyages need to change this dict to be keyed by Voyage and Crane.

SHP_CraneJobDrawingController
This is were it draws the jobs it builds up a external key dictionary SHP_CraneJobDrawingController:: allJobObjects which is of type CMUI_ObjectByRealX1Y1X2Y2Dict each entry is a CM_VoyageJob with the position to draw the job
All this entries are calculated from method SHP_JobControllerController ::getAllJobDrawControllersNew.  This method is on the SHP_JobControllerController class because need to figure out the x positions given (Zoom, Scale) and the job times from the CMUI_DrawScrollTimeLine and the y positions give the job bay from the CMUI_DrawCellVoyageOverview.

</text>
